<ARCH_SCAN_V3>
@ID: OUTBOUND_TRUST_AUDIT
@GOAL: IDENTIFY_RISKS_IN_EXTERNAL_DATA_EXCHANGE_AND_SSRF_VECTORS
@PARENT_CONTEXT: third_party_surface.protocol, critical_paths.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
# Маркеры внешних вызовов и динамических URL
OUTBOUND_CLIENTS: "(axios|fetch|request|http\.get|http\.post|resty|webClient|RestTemplate)"
DYNAMIC_URL_PATTERNS: "(\${|concat\(|format\(|url\.parse|uri\.builder)"

# Чувствительные данные для мониторинга утечек
LEAK_CANDIDATES: "(apiKey|secret|token|password|auth_header|private_key|PII)"
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<CONTEXT_MAP>
[EGRESS_POINT] <- {match: {{OUTBOUND_CLIENTS}}, scope: "FUNCTION_CALL"}
[URL_BUILDER]  <- {match: {{DYNAMIC_URL_PATTERNS}}, context: "URL_CONSTRUCTION"}
[INTERNAL_DATA] <- {match: {{LEAK_CANDIDATES}}}
</CONTEXT_MAP>

<ASSERTIONS>
# Логические инварианты внешнего доверия
! ([URL_BUILDER] -> [EGRESS_POINT]) & !VALIDATED : "CRITICAL: SSRF risk. Dynamic URL construction for outbound request without whitelist/sanitization."
! ([EGRESS_POINT] -> [INTERNAL_DATA]) & !ENCRYPTED : "HIGH: Sending sensitive internal data to external API without proper masking/encryption."
? ([EGRESS_POINT].response -> [APP]) & !VALIDATED : "MEDIUM: Implicit trust in external API response. Missing schema validation for inbound data."
! ([EGRESS_POINT] -> !TLS) : "HIGH: Outbound communication over unencrypted channel (HTTP)."
</ASSERTIONS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. ENUMERATE_EGRESS:
   - Identify all points in the code where [EGRESS_POINT] is invoked[cite: 66].
   - Map destinations: Are they static (hardcoded) or dynamic (user-provided)?
2. SSRF_VECTORS_SCAN:
   - Trace data flow from [INGRESS] (from entry_points.protocol) to [URL_BUILDER].
   - Flag any path where a user-controlled string influences the host, port, or path of an outbound request.
3. CREDENTIAL_LEAK_AUDIT:
   - Analyze headers and payloads of [EGRESS_POINT][cite: 70].
   - Ensure [INTERNAL_DATA] (like DB passwords or internal tokens) never leaks into external requests.
4. INBOUND_TRUST_VERIFICATION:
   - For each [EGRESS_POINT] response, check if the system validates the structure/content before using it in [APP][cite: 68, 71].
   - Flag "Blind Trust" where response data is directly used in logic or stored in [ZONE_SEC].
5. PROTOCOL_DOWNGRADE_CHECK:
   - Verify if the client forces HTTPS/TLS and rejects self-signed certificates in production[cite: 64].
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
GENERATE_OUTBOUND_REPORT:
  - TARGET_SERVICE | URL_TYPE (Static/Dynamic) | SENSITIVE_DATA_SENT | RESPONSE_VALIDATION
FILTER: RISK >= MEDIUM
VISUALIZE: "Mermaid graph showing Data_Flow: Internal_Service -> External_API (Red arrow if dynamic URL)."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</ARCH_SCAN_V3>